\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Whereabouts were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 In {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Abbotsford{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, Edinburgh, just the other side of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Morningside Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 How long did you stay in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 'Til - I was seventeen, now that would be 1924.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 And then you moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
We moved into a furnished flat - at the top of this stair, I was - my father was drowned in that year and I was left with a woman guardian and - we were fi
ve years in - the top flat and then she bought this flat in my name and I haven't lived in it continuously because I've been away to jobs and college and so on, but I've lived in it more than anywhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 So you've always bee in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Edinburgh{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 have you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Apart from when you've been away working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes. You can put it that way. I would have to start counting years, I don't think I could do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you have any brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Forty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 He was born in Greenock, and his ancestors came from Ura.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 He was a professor of Education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Had he always been in education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well he
 had a very great struggle, he got into the teaching profession through the pupil teacher system. And then when he was twenty he went to a training college in Glasgow? I suppose Jordan Hill but I don't know what one it was, and - then he taught in the vil
l
age school at Eckefachen for - I don't quite know how long but between ten and fifteen years and saved money and finally got to Edinburgh University in his thirties. Mm. Paid twelve - shillings a week for his lodgings. He took a degree First Class Honours
 in Mental Philosophy, and then he was - a lecturer - at Bangor in Wales in the Education Department for a bit and then he was a lecturer in the Education Department in Edinburgh, and then he was made professor in 1903.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 And that was his job until he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Until he died, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did he ever have any casual or part time jobs as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Not paid ones, he did a tremendous amount of unpaid work. To do with education, he was the - finally the Chairman of the Education Committee. It was an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6886513\charrsid3623088 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 d hoc body then, you had special elections for it, but he was on - he was on the Heriot Trust, he was on - the Provincial Committee for the training of teachers - governing body of \{BLANK\}
 Academy, St Bride's School, St George's School, he started the women's hostels at Trade Miller. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was your father ever out of work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No. I don't think so, I mean not as far as I know and I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Thirty-eight, very nearly thirty-nine but she was still thirty-eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 From Yorkshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Had she any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6886513\charrsid3623088 q}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
uite a lot. She left school at thirteen and was in the Post Office in Middlesborough, and - for two years. And then s
he was - according to her own story she was seven years - in Tarpaully in Cheshire with an uncle who had a shop and a not very efficient wife and she partly looked after his children and partly helped in the shop. There's a gap somewhere because the years
 
don't add up right, but - she - I think she must have done something else - between, or been more than seven years there or something, and then she was the first secretary at the London School of Economics. And I've got a - letter from her saying that she
 
hated being in the town amongst bricks and mortar but of course it's not everywhere that I can get a hundred a year. That was a hundred a year. And that was regarded as a marvellous salary at that time. Mm hm. And - then her health began to break down, sh
e
 had tuberculosis and - they sent her to Switzerland for the winter on full pay. And - she came back with her tuberculosis better but - her heart was worse and she'd had valvular disease from childhood but it was discovered at that point. And she worked a
 
bit more for them and then she broke down again and - went to Cornwall for a year and a half and they gave her books to index, actually the doctor told her she'd only about a year to live but that didn't seem to be - wasn't true. And then she came back to
 
them again, and broke down a third time, and that time they sacked her. Well by that time she'd got very friendly with Miss Webb, Sidney Webb's sister, and - they went together - and lived on a farm in Aberdeenshire and she got tutoring from the schoolmas
ter and she managed to pass her University prelim. And she came to Edinburgh University - but she didn't manage to take a degree and she couldn't cope with logic and metaphysics and she was sent to my father for help, and that was how she met him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 After they were married did she ever work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No. Well she typed his lectures but I mean she didn't do any paid work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What was the address where you were as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 12 Abbotsford Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Can you remember how many rooms there were in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Well - now - it's - just as a snap answer I'd say eight, but I'd better count. You - are you counting kitchen and everything like that or just - sitting rooms and bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Reception rooms and bedrooms and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Oh yes, well - n
ow - the study and the dining room downstairs, that's two, and drawing room upstairs is three. One, two, three, four bedrooms upstairs, that's seven, and there was a maid's bedroom in the sort of depths near the kitchen, so that is really eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Eight rooms plus a kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was there a bathroom in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did anyone else other than your parents and yourself live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well, yes, Miss Webb lived with us - she was my mother's friend and she sort of helped o
ut with the housework. And - she was the one that became my guardian after - my parents death. And we had - up to the time of the firs war we had two maids. And then we had one - most of the time but it got more and more broken. But I think - we had what 
was called a lady's help at the time of my father's death, but anyway we had somebody more often than not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 And did these maids live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 They lived in the house, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What did you actually call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 By their first names mostly. There was one that I remember being called Thomson, I don't know why she got her second name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What were their jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well - cook and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6886513\charrsid3623088 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088  house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6886513\charrsid3623088 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 table}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6886513\charrsid3623088 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 maid, and I think they probably more or less - did the duties that that implies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was there somebody who came in to clean the house as well?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No. No, the house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6886513\charrsid3623088 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 table}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6886513\charrsid3623088 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
maid did the cleaning. Well I think - she may have done the upstairs rooms and the cook may have done the downstairs rooms, but I'm not quite sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 They organised it between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes. But Miss Webb always got up for a long time at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6886513\charrsid3623088 
half past six and cleaned the f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 lues because they couldn't be relied on to do it properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did they have a room where they could sit by themselves when they weren't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No, they had the kitchen and it was quite a spacious kitchen, but they didn't actually have a room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did your mother supervise the housework herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well - she and Miss Webb did it between them, I wouldn't like to say which of them did more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you know if they gave any moral guidance to the servants at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I don't really know for certain, I would think they probably did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What about the servants and the family, were they at ease with each other or were they very much that they were the maids?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
I think they were rather kept apart because - we had one maid that I got rather friendly with, I mean I kept going to the kitchen door and asking for water for some game I was - playing, and I got stopped from that, I mean
 rather gently but it was stopped.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What did they call the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I suppose they called them Professor Darroch and Mrs Darroch and Miss Webb.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 And what would they call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Jane. They did call me Jane, yes. Yes. I also - originally - t
old that there were two somebody's in the kitchen, which I think was a rather - odd word.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 When they were in the house did they have any free time to do as they liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well - I think they had - what was called days out. I think probably something
 like two half days a week but I don't remember. But my - impression is that they went out - more than they stayed in. The one I remember clearly of many that we had during the war was engaged to a corporal and I seem to remember the corporal coming. So h
e may have come in the - into the kitchen and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6886513\charrsid3623088 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
at with her but - on the whole my impression is that they mostly went out. In their free time, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was the washing done at home or was it sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I think it was probably done at home but I'm not sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 How about the family clothes, did the servants look after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
No. No, my mother did - the mending and a lot of dressmaking. Miss Webb could dress make too but - I think it was my mother that made most of my clothes. And I think she probably made her own. And I remember her knitting black stockings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Who was responsible for repairs and improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I don't think I know, I suppose my father but I should they probably discussed it together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Would he get tradesmen to come in and do anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Yes, I mean remember rooms being - papered and painted and being told what the new paper was going to be. But I don't quite know who chose it. Or who decided when it was to be done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were any of the maids responsible for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No. Just for the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you have any jobs to do in the house when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
No, my mother was terribly keen to make me - into a blue stocking, I mean, I think she'd been deprived of education herself and she wanted me to
 be academic and she would never let me help in the house - in case it might interfere with my lessons. And I was about thirty before I discovered how much I liked housework. I love cooking, I don't like cleaning very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Can you remember who put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 My mother.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 At what age did you start putting yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Oh - I don't quite know, possibly about - nine or ten, but I'm not really sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 And you had a room to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No, I slept with my mother - I think until 
I was about ten. She was very ill when I was six. And I was certainly separated from her then, she nearly died, she had pleurisy. And was terribly ill for about three weeks, and I think Miss Webb may have come in and slept with me then but I'm not sure. B
ut I remember being definitely given a room to myself when I was ten and - feeling that this was a privilege.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You had a bathroom in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 When did you generally have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I should think once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Would it be at bath}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6886513\charrsid3623088 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 time, after your bath or did you have a bath every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Had a bath every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Perhaps a Sunday that you would get your clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I think it might have been. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Where did the adults eat their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 In the dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were you allowed to join them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you remember the cooking equipment in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Mm - not very well, I mean I can remember the - there was - a kitchen range. That was - that was what was used, yes. That's all yo
u want to know, it isn't all - all pots and pans and that, no. Yes. Yes. I remember my mother being very indignant because we had a maid who was a miner's daughter and they got cheap coal and - their mother cooked with gas, as - and my mother thought this
 was terrible - and luxury and this was - or was it Miss Webb, I'm not sure which of them, but anyway I can remember - a feeling of being shocked at this.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What time would breakfast be usually eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Who was present for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Everybody, I was a bit unpunctual and - I'd got into or was a bit occasional.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you remember what you usually had to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I always had a boiled egg. And I had cocoa and my mother had coffee and my father and Miss Webb had tea. And an
 auntie came to stay and made fun of us for - for having this arrangement. But I don't remember what the grown ups ate, I should think quite possibly bacon and egg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Would you ever have anything different, perhaps on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I don't think so. I
 think I was rather a fussy child about food and when they got something I would eat they were inclined to stick to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was your next meal lunch time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Lunch time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Who would be present then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Oh - all of us. Father and my mother, M
iss Webb and me, yes, he came home. There might be very occasional times when he went out but not often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Can you remember what you'd have to eat for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 That was the main meal, it would be meat - on A Sunday it was roast meat, roast joint. An
d - two vegetables and Yorkshire pudding, and I think very often a - a - an apple pie or something of that sort and custard, real custard with an egg in it. In nice little pretty glasses, and - later on in the week it would be some other kind of meat, me 
- I remember beef olives as a common thing. I can't quite remember what else. Mince sometimes. We had meat every day. Except - in the war, we had lentil rissoles sometimes and I think we perhaps had fish occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 After lunch what would be your next meal?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Afternoon tea, between four and five. And that was tea and bread and butter and sometimes cakes. I remember my father used to take - almost attacks of eating a lot of very sweet cakes and this would go on for a while and then it would stop again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you have supper at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Yes, that was at seven. And - very often it was eating up the cold joint from Sunday, and - I think perhaps sometimes fish, I don't really quite remember. I remember herrings on - very often on a summer holida
y when my - father and I - oh much later than we meant to be and my mother was very upset and I remember sitting down to these herrings with a sort of sense of guilt. Yes. And I remember Miss Web trying to make nice little dishes to tempt my mother's appe
tite because she wouldn't eat much at all, and there was sometimes things made specially for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Can you remember if any of the following were made in the house, bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I should think possibly, certainly marmalade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Bottled fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Wines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Would that be the cook that would make the jam and so on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Miss Webb - mostly, I remember her sitting - a 
huge vast jelly pan that I only got rid of quite recently and - dropping peel into it. For marmalade. The maids may have done it sometimes but mostly Miss Webb, she was very fond of housework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were fruit and vegetables grown in the garden at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
In the war we dug up a strip of the lawn and grew quite a lot of vegetables. And we had four gooseberry bushes in one of the borders - even before the war I think. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Otherwise they'd be bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Who did the garden usually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
My mother did as much as she could, she - she was very fond of it, but she wasn't strong enough to cope with the whole thing and every now and again she got a gardener.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was there ever any livestock kept for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes, I had goldfish. 
Which all died because - we didn't know about them needing oxygen. And then I had a tortoise that lived for - two and a half years and he died because he got up too soon from hibernating and went back again - I think so much better to keep them in the hou
s
e, we had him in the garden by a dump of great big - pile of turfs and things, and we had a canary that lived about a year and a half and then died, and - we had doves that were stolen. They were kept outside in a big cage and - someone took them in the s
ummer holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Who was responsible for looking after these pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well I think I was supposed to be but I - think I did a fair amount but I think my mother supervised me and did some things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did the servants and yourself have the same food or was it different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 As far as I know it was the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Whereabouts did the servants eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 In the kitchen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were you allowed to talk at meal times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was there, or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
I think I probably was allowed to choose, I have a - sort of feeling of having been a - a very bad child about this and - being more or less forced to eat - some things, just because they were necessary and I wouldn't
 - I mean I can remember as a small child my mother sitting beside me with a boiled egg and saying Doctor Ormerod}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6886513\charrsid3623088  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
says you must eggs because of the albumenoids, and it amazes me that I too in that word but I'm sure I did. And - in the end I gave way and di
d and then I got to like them. But I didn't take green vegetables until I was quite old - I was sent to stay with a very bossy aunt and uncle when I was fourteen and they made me eat everything and I think that broke it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What happened if you left something uneaten on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Oh nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were you taught to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were you allowed to bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 When were you allowed to leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I had to say things when I get down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were you allowed to leave before everyone else had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I'm not quite sure, I don't think we did - I - I can't remember why I change why it changed but I think it did change from time to time.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Who generally served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You mean in the sense of being - I think the maids brought it in, or the house table}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6886513\charrsid3623088 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 m
aid brought it in and - I can't remember now who carved. But anyway - one or other of my parents served it. And - I - don't remember what happened when we got down to one maid, when we got down to no maids obviously Miss Webb must have brought it in from 
the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were you served in any order, for instance was your father always served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I've a feeling I was always served first. But I - I'm not quite sure. Think that I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well she wa
s a tremendously vivacious person but I was always so very frightened of her, I mean there was - I remember noticing at quite an early age that I would tell Miss Webb things I wouldn't tell her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was she an affectionate person or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes, she was very affectionate but she was also very harsh when she was angry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Would you have gone to Miss Webb if you were worried about something rather than to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well not always - I mean I can remember telling my mother things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What about your father, was he an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well, he was terribly reserved and wrapped up in his work, and I wasn't - I wasn't frightened of him but he was terribly busy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Would you have gone to him with any worries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well I don't think
 I ever did, I - I don't think there was any - sort of obvious feeling that I oughtn't but I don't seem to remember that I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you know what kind of person your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well I think my mother wanted me to be an academic success.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 And your father too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 My father got rather worried when I was in my teens. Because he fe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6886513\charrsid3623088 l}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 t that my mother had dominated me too much and made me too academic. And - also I had a - very elaborate fantasy life that I - I mean they
 knew I had it and - he was worried about that. And I was rather shy, I mean I think he knew that I wasn't sort of looking very well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did they consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well my mother was deeply religious and she once said the most important thing in life is to be good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What did your parents think about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
I don't think the question - oh I think my mother once said she thought strong language was useful as a relief but - it was so rare that it didn't come into one's life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what happened generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well - when I was - small I remember once being spanked and it was a terribly - painful memory for years and years and years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Who did the spanking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
My mother. And - I mean actually I was psychoanalysed in my later twenties because the affect I think went back to my mother's severity and this was - this was a thing that I alw
ays talked about, and of course you've got to face the fact that a lot of children were spanked and didn't react so badly to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Perhaps being an only child you had nothing to compare it with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 That may be, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did your father have any form of discipline for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Not very much. I do remember my father once hitting me but I didn't take it very seriously, and I don't think he meant it very seriously. But later on my mother scolded me and I was terribly frightened of her. I mean if I got 
- a report at school, I always told the children I got another row at home, and - she looked at all my exercise books and if I'd less than about seven or eight out of ten she wanted to know why.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about
 how to behave from both your parents, or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
I - superficially I think from my mother, but - since I've been middle aged I realize that my father wasn't - terribly happy with my mother and that he was f
aithful to her and was as kind to her as he could be, and - I think that really means a very great deal to me now, you know, I feel inclined now to say that there was far more real compassion in him than there was in - some modern people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was a birthday any different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Oh - oh yes, it was kept - I mean I always got a present and - sometimes some sort of treat, I don't remember that so much as the present, but I remember a general feeling of a happy day, and I remember the - exci
tement about - the other peoples birthdays too. I can remember the day when my mother came down and expected to see something on the table and we told her to go and look out of the window and it - it was a wheelbarrow for the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you remember anything the family did together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
I think my Christmas party was on Christmas Day. We had a Christmas tree and I'm told that the first time we had a Christmas tree which was when I was quite small I was just absolutely dazed by the be
auty of it. But I don't really remember that I remember being shut out of the drawing room because there was a surprise in it, but I - I don't remember the thing itself. But - but I went to school when I was eight and after that we always had a party from
 
our school friends and we always had the Christmas tree. Until the war came and you couldn't get them, and - then we had a bran tub and they got present sout of the bran tub but they - up ptil then they got presents off the tree, and - played party games.
 
And I really think a tree with candles is much more lovely than with electric lights and - I think in those days it wasn't dangerous because everybody knew the fire risk, I think nowadays it wouldn't be because - people would be - unused to it. And - my f
a
ther - used to come out of his shell and be terribly nice at parties, we - used to play a game called the sea and her children which is - on the same principle as musical chairs, I mean there's one seat too - few but - one person is Father Ocean and every
b
ody else is fish and seaweed and things and - he calls them all - out and run about and then he says, the sea is troubled, the sea is troubled, and as soon as he says that you've all got to find a seat, well he used to - always start this off by being Fat
her Ocean. And - at the - towards the end of the party he used to make us scramble for sweets, he used to line us up at one end of the drawing room and throw, I think they were fondants with some sort of hard sweets for us to scramble for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were there any musical instruments in your home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 There was a piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Who played it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 My mother - and - Miss Webb a little bit buy mostly my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was there anyone who sang in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 She sang, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you ever have sort of musical evenings at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Obviously you would have plenty of books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Newspapers and magazines as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 And your mother and father would both read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did they ever read aloud to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No, but my mother read aloud to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did they ever play games with you as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Yes. I remember my mother playing draughts with me quite a lot. And when I was fourteen - I was promoted to play - play three handed bisique on summer holiday
. My father thought he hadn't had a summer holiday if he didn't play three handed bisique every night, and I think my mother didn't like it very much and - and - this time she got out of it and I had to do it instead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you remember a funeral in your family as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No. My grandparents both died but they died in Yorkshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well not relations because there weren't any in Edinburgh, but friends quite a lot
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Who generally took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 My mother. Until - after I was - six she didn't go out much because she got delicate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were you taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes, every day practically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was that with your mother too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 That was with my mother until I was six and then with Miss Webb.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes. Summer holidays for country walks and sometimes on Sunday mornings for country walks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you remember any special outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you me
an with ey - all the family? Don't seem to remember occasions when we were all there, I remember being - driven round Arthur's Seat - on my eighth birthday in some sort of - cab or carriage. This was mainly because my mother had been ill and was convalesc
ing and we thought a drive would be good for her but - I'd been promoted to get up for early breakfast for the first time, and somehow this was all part of the morning, but I don't think my father was there, I mean he might even have been working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You said you went away to the country for holidays, did you go every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Yes. They - rented a house - at the seaside - until I was six, and then it got more difficult, I think probably because of the war and after that it was more often country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 How long would you go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 A month, and sometimes six weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did all the family go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 And Miss Webb?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 And Miss Webb. And the -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Would you take the maids with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were your clothes always new when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 And shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did your father ever help with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did he ever look after you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I think he did a bit but probably mostly when I was small, there's a sort of - Edinburgh 
story that goes around that somebody looked over our garden wall when I was two, and - they saw him come up with an armful of books and papers intending to work but he didn't, he spent the whole afternoon playing with me, and being terribly patient, but I
 - I just wanted to go in and out some little gap somewhere and - I don't quite know what he had to doubt he spent the whole afternoon being patient and playing with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Can you tell me how you spent Saturday when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well in the morn
ing I was usually doing - prep for school, I can't remember what I did before I went to school, probably went shopping with Miss Webb I should think and then played. I don't think it was much different from any other day, but after I went to school I was 
c
ertainly doing prep and we always had an English essay of sometimes a scripture essay and I wasn't good at essay, and it was frightfully - and - oh I think this was when I was in my teens, we always had jam tart for lunch and I always felt that was a grea
t treat after this awful essay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 How about a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Sunday we - mostly went for a country walk, but - always with my father and sometimes - usually with Miss Webb I think, but I'm not sure, sometimes just with my father I went I think and then - 
four times a year we went to church because he went to represent the University, you know there were seats kept in St Giles for Professors. So we went to St Giles on those four - Sundays. And I remember my mother going once - 'cos I remember astonishment 
a
t seeing her kneeling on a stone floor, and - I think I had a feeling that God must be very powerful if he could do that. And - then when I was thirteen I - wanted to belong to the Church of England because it was the church that she'd grown up with and I
 
started going to St Mary's cathedral on Sunday mornings with Miss Webb. And that lasted about a year, and then I went to stay with this bossy aunt, and - I don't know, she was very critical of people and I thought if that was what the Church of England pr
oduced I didn't like it much. And I think probably after that I went back to not going to church. I was finally - baptized and confirmed when I was a student at Cambridge. Then that's after what you were asking about.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you have different clothes to wear on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
I should think I probably did. But I do remember us having different toys because we had tea in the drawing room, and there were toys that were kept up there and I regarded them as a sort of Sunday treat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were all your other meals in the dining room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes. Except for the Sunday tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were you allowed to play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did your parents think it was wrong to work on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I think they did, I - I've a slight feeling that I didn't do need
le work - it wasn't much frustration because I wasn't very keen on it anyway but I - I think I - I think I did feel that you shouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 The only time you went to church was to St Giles? Did you go to the Sunday school or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No. I had lots of religious teaching from my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was that religious teaching only on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
No, it was - well I was taught to say prayers when I was five I think but even before that she talked about God - sort of casually when it came to my mind and she sang hymns a great deal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were there ever family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was your father interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Don't think he was very interested in - party politics, I think he - probably v
oted Conservative but I don't even know, but he was very interested in local admin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 stration.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 And was your mother interested at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 She had been a Radical in her youth. In fact, when she was in - Middlesborough in her youth she had the experienc
e of a working man turning Radical because of her. And then she became Conservative and sort of looked on being a Radical as a kind of youthful folly, and - I think she was very disappointed in the working class as being somehow worse people that she thou
ght they would be. But I - I don't quite - know when the c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
ange came or how, but she had a great friend who was an active Labour party member so I think she still had some sympathy with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you remember your father or mother voting in general elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well of course my mother - wouldn't have the vote. Yes, I suppose she would the last few years of her life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 In 1918 I think it was property owners over thirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Oh yes, well then no she wouldn't 'cos she - she died in 1922. I don't remember my father voting, I suppose he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did he ever take part in any political activities at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well of course he stood for the - Education Committee and I delivered leaflets for him when I was thirteen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was your father under any sort of pressure from the university what party he would vote for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No. I don't think so, not as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 When your parents weren't doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well my mother was very fond of reading, and - she play
ed the piano and sang to it. She played with me. She - did the garden whenever she was well enough.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did she have any interests outside of her home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 She - I remember her making things for the garden fete at school. She made - pretty little scent
 sachets, she used to make four dozen of them in different colours, that sold very well, and she used to make real lemonade from real lemons in a great big earthen jug. I don't think she had very much outside the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
They went to the theatre every now and again, my - my parents, leaving Miss Webb at home I think - when I was little I remember that, I remember my mother having a beautiful - blue satin dress, I've still got it put away in the box}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 room,
 and - I think I didn't like it 'cos I didn't like being left, I remember the sort of feeling of excitement about it. And then I was taken to Peter Pan and I was taken to a theatre every now and again with one or both of them - not - very often, two or th
ree times a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did your father - when did he usually get home from work in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Well, he - was usually at home a lot of the day because he only gave one hour's lecture from nine to ten, but then he was - a very great deal of the time s
hut up inside his study reading and writing, and a very great deal more of the time he was rushing about sitting on committees.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 How many evenings a week would he spend at home would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Think he was pretty often at home in the lat evening after - supper. And I think the committees were mostly - probably afternoons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was he a member of any kind of clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I've vague recollections he talked about the club and that it was somewhere down in Princes Street, but I - I can't remember how o
ften he went or what he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Your mother wouldn't go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No. I think it was probably one of these all male affairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did your father take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 He played golf. Was very good at it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did he ever attend horse racing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Not as long as I know. I think my mother probably did in her youth because she - spent the middle part of her childhood at Redcar and there were races.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 As a child who did you usually play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Well I played a great deal alone, I mean I - had other children brought to tea with me but I used to be terribly shy and - very occasionally we'd have fun together but mostly I was so shy I was glad wh
en they were gone. And then I went to school when I was eight and after that I played with school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
friends. A fair amount but - I was alone a lot of the time in the holidays and I think I was rather bored sometimes. I mean it was a case of having a school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 f
riend to tea, I can remember one girl - coming to tea and that we played cricket on the lawn, and I can remember another girl that I used to go and see and she was very good at needlework and she taught me how to make various things for my mother and - an
other day we dressed up - as Oberon and Titania. But - I think this was every now and again that you sort of went out to see somebody or somebody came to see you. It wasn't regular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What sort of games did you play when you were on your own then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
I drew a lot, and I - made paper birds and cut - coloured them and cut them out and had sort of fantasies about them, I had a lot of fantasies about birds, and I had toy animals. And a lot of toy - animals that floated in my bath and had quite an elaborat
e
 sort of story about - them, I mean there were - fathers and - mothers and children and so on, and I don't think I had an idea at that age how babies came because I remember you know fathers with children and no mother and mother with children and no fath
e
r. And - I didn't play with dolls, there was a doll - dressed in the same clothes as I had, but I was never very interested in it. Oh I played with dolls very occasionally but not much, I think it was mostly animals. Oh and I had balls and - again they we
re sort of people and - I - kicked them round the garden and spanked them for going the wrong way and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were you allowed to get dirty when you were playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes. Nobody minded.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was there anyone that your parents discouraged you from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well - once one of my school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 friends got - friendly with two girls that - that I wanted to have to my Christmas party and they wouldn't let me, and I think - it probably because they were slightly lower social class - although
 - there wasn't any reason given. But I - otherwise no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I belonged to the Girl Guides and was very keen on it. We had a company at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you go away camping or anything at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 When you were at school did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Well I played - and we had - I think this from a fairly big - it might be beyond the age you're asking about but we had an art teacher who - encouraged us to sketch in the summer holidays and 
bring them back for criticism and I got very keen on sketching as a result of that and I still - paint every now and again when I've got time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you have any collections of anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Oh I collected wild flowers on the summer holidays, and - ga
ve them to the school and eventually had to take them back because they hadn't room for them, and - I think I collected cigarette cards at one stage, not terribly seriously but they were nice things to have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you do any gardening at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I ha
d a little bit where I was allowed to grow annuals for myself. I can't remember if I helped my mother, I might have done a wee bit I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You spoke about going for walks with your father, did you go for walks with anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 With Miss Webb,
 and on the summer holidays - she would take me if my father wanted to golf which was about half the days I should think, and - I don't remember if I ever went - alone with her in Edinburgh, I think it was my father and Miss Webb and me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you have a bicycle when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No, not 'til I was a student.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you take part in any sports?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Well I was very bad at it, I made a - feeble attempt to learn to play tennis. In my last year or two at school, oh I played - basket ball and cricket when I was small but both very badly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You spoke about going to see Peter Pan, did you go to the theatre much at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well, about - I should think probably only three or four times a year, perhaps not even that, but I enjoyed it tremend
ously when I did go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What about concerts and music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Not much I - think perhaps concerts very occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you go to the cinema while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes, it was only just beginning but - I remember seeing Little Women, 
and I remember seeing Charlie Chaplin going up a moving staircase the wrong way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you have pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes, I had sixpence a week but I'd no idea what to do with it, I put it in a money box.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You didn't spend it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No. No, I was a funny child some ways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You had Miss Webb to help your mother look after the house, if your mother was ill it was Miss Webb that would run the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes, it was, and she worked very hard and she nursed my mother at home through quite a lot of very nasty illnesses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You said you didn't have any relatives living nearby, did your parents have many friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I think they probably had a fair amount. I find it difficult to distinguish what were real friends what were people that they had to be 
polite to. I mean there was Mrs Barger who was the wife of the Professor of Medical Chemistry and I know my mother liked her very much and - I remained friendly with her until she died, she - spent her old age in Hampstead and I used to go and see her the
r
e. And - there was Doctor Morgan who - was eventually the head of my house training college, he was a - very close friend of my father's, they used to golf together. And - his wife came to the house sometimes and we went to their house sometimes. And ther
e
 was - Doctor Lauder was my father's friend, they were both born in Greenock, but I think they met in Bangor, but anyway - he was a lecturer in Agricultural Chemistry and they were - very close friends and he became my legal guardian after - my father's d
e
ath, my other legal guardian, Miss Webb was the - other - the one that lived with me, and - he used to come on Sunday evenings and play with me and - was great fun because he pretended to be some sort of wild animal. And - my mother always read aloud to m
e on Sunday evenings the Wind in the Willows, I was so fond of it I wanted it over and over again and he always came and inquired whether the Toad was in to the
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did your mother and father share the same friends or did they each have their own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
I think they more or less shared the same. There was a - oh think it was Professor Ken Smith, though I'm not sure - or - or was there Mr Kemp, I think it was - I think it was Mr Kemp and I think he became Professor Kemp Smith because he - took the n
ame of smith for some reason, he used to come and see my father and they used to laugh and laugh and laugh and you always knew when he was there because there was so much laughter coming out of the study, but - the rest of us didn't see him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 When people called in was it by invitation or did they drop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Well there was this system of having at home days, and - I think probably they mostly came on my mother's at home day, but I think some people came - just dropping in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Would they get something to eat or drink when they came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 They would get tea, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 And at the at home they would get something as well would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 On the at home day they would get tea. I remember my mother telling me that if you paid a formal call you only stay
ed twenty minutes and didn't take your hat of. But - and of course in that case I think you probably wouldn't get tea but I think most of the people that came to us stayed longer than that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did your parents go to visit other people as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 They
 did, yes. I think they probably did some formal calls because I remember a box with visiting cards in it, you left a visiting card if you came and found people out. But I remember going to tea with the Morgans. I think - I can't remember when but I think
 fairly early. I should remember where else I was taken to tea with shouldn't I. I think I don't remember - I think I probably rather hated being taken out to tea and sort of - blotted it out from my memory, but I'm not very clearly about -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 How about neighbours, did they call in at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
There was a - yes, there was a lady next door called Miss McFarland, I think we mostly went to her, she bred canaries and I was terribly thrilled with the canaries. And I remember her seeing - I remember seeing he
r give a canary a poached egg because it was breeding. Mm, yes, she did. And she was very nice, she lived in the upper flat of a - flat at number fourteen and - she eventually lost her memory. She had a devoted maid called Jessie that was awfully good to 
her and stayed with her 'til she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 People often made their own amusements in those days, if your parents had friends in how did they occupy themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Don't remember anything except talking. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 They didn't have music together or play any kind of games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
A lot of people divided society into different social classes or groups, in the time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class or group and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes I did, I think I - fe
lt that everybody was inferior who didn't go to a school. Where the parents paid the full fees, the full cost. Yes, I mean - I think I hardly met anybody, except my school friends, I think I looked enviously at these elementary children because they were 
allowed to wear scarlet tam'o' shanters and all sorts of bright things and we had to wear navy blue and white. But I think I also felt they were inferior.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What would you call that then, the group of people that didn't go to fee paying schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Either working class or lower class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What would you call the other ones then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I suppose middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was there an upper class in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well, yes, there was, I mean I think I was vaguely aware that there were - aristocracies, sort
 of Lords and Dukes but didn't expect to know them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 And you'd consider yourself as middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Because you went to a fee paying school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well now schoo
l friends, father - I remember one girl being considered inferior because they said her father was a shop assistant at Maules, actually he did Maules advertisements. Now another girl's father was a - an engineer in India, another was an army doctor in Ind
ia, there were an awful lot of Colonial girls. I can't think what Amy McLarens father did, she was a sister of Marie McLaren but - can't think - an awful lot of them, I can't remember what they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 It was a fair cross section was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 It was - El
sa Anderson was - big shopkeeper, her father was a big shopkeeper, I think he was connected with Grants. It was - I would say - professional and - the bigger shopkeepers - mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What sort of people belonged to the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I think manual
 workers and small shopkeepers. Actually my aunts on my mother's side were - had a stationers shop which my grandparents had, and I remember then this was after I was grown up, I should think I might have been - I don't know what age I was, 'cos I can't r
emember when it was, I was certainly grown up, they asked me - whether I looked down on shopkeepers implying that they hoped I didn't and at that time I was able to say no quite confidently but with a slight feeling that at an earlier age I wouldn't.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Yes, I can, I mean even Miss Webb - Miss Webb lived 'til I was over thirty and lived together in this flat, and I remember she gave the charwoman tea out
 of an inferior cup and said because she might break it, and I disliked this very much but - I mean I revolted very much against all this and I eventually joined the Labour party and - I was a Labour party member for about eighteen years - and I always be
en very careful to - sort of - treat working class people as equals in the way of being polite to them and giving them the best china and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were you ever told to curtsey to anybody?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What about your parents, were you ev
er conscious of people showing respect to your parents? Calling them sir or madam and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
I don't remember, I think people probably did. I've some - recollection of my mother - or Miss Webb, I'm not sure which, being upset either beca
use a maid said cheerio to her or because she thought a maid might say cheerio to her, I'm not sure even which it was, but there certainly was a - a - a division. And actually I still get furious with people who call me dear, I mean I mostly - bottle it u
p but I - I don't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 It was the Morningside district that you were brought up in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Who were considered the most important people in that particular area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Oh I don't think I know, because - I don't think I think in terms 
of areas. I mean I think the people that I probably thought of as important would be the other Professors at the university and - most of all the Principle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Your life really centred on the university?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes. I remember my father coming home one da
y - and he said terribly sadly, Sir William Turner's dying. And - he stopped talking in the middle of the meeting and we didn't get anything more from him, so I think he must have been at a Semester's meeting that he was taken ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What did you think about the clergy for instance, were they important or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes, I think I probably had respect for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 And teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You wouldn't come into contact with farmers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 The employers, were they important people or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
I suppose they were - one of my mother's uncles was a manager in an iron works in Middlesborough and I think - we thought he was important. But we were also conscious that he was a very nice man, I mean he was her favourite uncle. Farmers - oh
 this is beyond your period thought, as - when I was - fifteen after my mother's death we started going back to \{BLANK\}
 and we got very friendly with a family of my father's second cousins who had a farm and a hotel there and are - awfully nice people, I'm
 saying are because there's one still alive. And - was - they had a farm, that's the - out shearing in the - in the lambing season. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Farmers in Jura would perhaps be different from farmers on the mainland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes, I don't think I have - yes, 
my mother's - grandfather was a farmer at Altrinchham in North Yorkshire and she went to stay there as a child very often and - I think was very happy there and she - was present at the harvest home quite often, and she remembered seeing We Plough the Fie
lds and Scatter at the harvest thanks giving service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What sort of people would you say went to church, before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Before 1918? My feeling is that most people did. I remember - the head - mistress - as - there was some question of whether we sh
ould get a holiday on Good Friday and she asked for a show of hands as to how many would go to church if we did and about two thirds of us put our hands up. I think I - probably supposed that working class people didn't go so much, but I - I don't think I
 - know, I mean I think my feelings was of being rather unusual because I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you know much about the working class people in the Morningside area, did you come into contact with them much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Not an awful lot, I remember seeing a message boy with bare feet, and I think that must have been the spring of 1914.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Do you think the working class people in this particular area had the same standard of living or was there a division amongst the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you mean would they have a high standard in Morningside than in some other places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 In Morningside was the standard much the same in the working class, or was there a difference within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I don't think I know, I mean I know that - some of the - elementary schoolchildren had bare}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 feet, I mean I think perhaps a quarter and the others didn't, but that was the only thing I was conscious of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you know if some families were thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I don't think I was aware of t
hat, I was aware of my - parents having a problem about beggars, and mostly they wouldn't give. But - there was a Mrs Harkness that they had given to once and she kept coming back and back and they were sort of worried about what to do with her and whethe
r they should go on or whether they shouldn't go on. But, I think it was more - anxiety about poor people sort of - sponging on you with hard luck stories than anxiety about them being rough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Can you remember if there was a distinction between a craftsman and a labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No, probably there was but I can't remember it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You didn't come into contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes or did they treat people differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
I should think - my father was probably much more really friendly to the working classes than my mother was because he really was a working class origin, I don't quite know - what his father was, I think he may have been a rather unsuccessful small shop
keeper but - his family - were at least relatively poor and somehow relatively working class in their outlook and I was kept away from them, on various excuses, but I think it was really because of that and I get to know them until I was about thirty, and
 then I discovered they were mostly very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to any particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I think she saw herself as middle class, and probably rather precariously so because - her parents - her father was a
 teacher when he - married her grand-mother, and then he left and did some - job in connection with printing that didn't last long and then he opened this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 stationer\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088  shop that never did very well, well I think it did well enough to keep them but I think there was always - a bit of anxiety about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another, either up or down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well my father certainly moved up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you think he really saw himself as being middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes I do. I d
o. I think he - in many ways made a great effort to adapt to middle class standards, he had one or two - little habits like picking his nose that - and so on - that gave his origin away, and I think it said a lot for the society that they never bothered a
bout that. But he - he suddenly had to furnish this big house - with not only basic furniture, well he bought those chairs which I think are very nice, and - not only basic furniture but pictures and - he bought quite a decent collection of pictures.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Can you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
No, I don't - think so. I think it is a description I would use now of one or two people - as - meant as very high praise, but - I don't - known when I first heard it, I mean I've no clear recollection of it being applied to any particular person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Oh yes, indeed, there was a policeman came that we were friendly with, Mr Cary, that we used to stop and t
alk to in the street. But I was frightened of police-men in general and we remember being quite surprised that we sort of dared to be friendly with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What made you frightened of them, had you been told something that made you frightened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I suppose so but I don't know what.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 How do you think policemen generall treated people at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I've no idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 It was rented.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you ever see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Oh - well - he was Martin the baker and we bought the bread at his shop, but I don't remember actually seeing him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was he a good landlord in as much if you were needing something done, was it done to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I don't remember, I seem to remember - I suppose he would have to
 do all the - sort of repairs to the fabric but I don't remember much about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 It can't have been a struggle then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No, I'm sure it wasn't. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did your parents ever have a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I - don't - think so, my mother
 was very economical in the war, but I think that was more out of patriotism than because it was really necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was there anyone in the Morningside district that you can ever remember people disapproving of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Don't think so. Not in my chi
ldhood, no. Mm hm. I can remember them disapproving of the headmistress because - she said that the Guide Company was a cadet corps and they thought that was snobbish. Yes. It's rather odd, I mean it's a sort of a - a throw in the opposite direction from 
the main feeling but they did and - I really went worrying about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You didn't go to school until you were eight, were you given lessons by one of your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 By my mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 When did she start giving you lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 When I was five and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What sort of hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well it began with one hour in the mornings and - I think by the time I was eight it was about two and a half hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 That was alone was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 That was alone. She had - the idea that she'd like to have a 
little school of about six children belonging to friends, she had wanted to be a teacher and been stopped on health grounds, but this never happened and - I'm rather glad it didn't I mean I think it was getting too sort of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 cramping}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088  to be too much with her, I think I needed to be out and meet a variety of - people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did she make you wear a uniform at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 She didn't, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 How did you feel about her as a teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well, I think the day when she first brought me in from play and set me d
own and said, now then lessons, I felt rather awful. But I think I quite enjoyed it - most of the time. I remember an awful day when I said is was a preposition and she stopped the lesson abruptly and said I must be tired but - I felt very crushed. But I 
don't remember much sort of - unpleasantness and she helped me very far and she had me doing square root. And I used to recite - I used to learn poem by heart and every now and again recite it to my father over lunch.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did she emphasise certain things as important in life, such as manners, tidiness, punctuality and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Well she emphasised manners a fair amount, I mean I wasn't supposed to put my elbows on the table. Tidiness - I can't quite remember. Yes, I mean I'm a sort of a mixture now, I m
ean I'm tidy in parts and untidy in parts and I feel I always was but I can't remember much about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you have any form of punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well mostly scolding. Mm hm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What kind of things were you punished for? Talking about lessons now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Oh this just in connection with lessons, oh - no, I don't think there was much - well yes I suppose for making bad mistakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You were taught until you were eight and then you went to schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Which school was it that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 It was St Bride's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was that a boarding school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
That was a day - well it was - they had boarders but I mean I went as a day pupil, they had - when they were biggest they had about eighty boarders and - about a hundred and - seventy day pupils I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 All girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 All girls, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was it a private school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Private - well it was a private school until the 1918 Education Act, and then it had a board of governors and a salaried headmistress. It was all - it was - it went back to the 1830's.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 When you first started going to school what time of the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Nine o'clock I think or round about anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 When did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 To begin with I think I came back at one. And - as I got older 
there were gradually afternoon lessons at half past two that - tended to get more and more, half past two to four, or half past two 'til quarter past three sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You came home for your lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 And I came home for my lunch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 How long would it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 About - ten minutes I think, maybe a quarter of an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Miss Webb. And - I can't remember how old I was when I started going alone. I think probably not - ter
ribly old but I mean maybe about ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Absolutely loved it, I was fri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 htened of going because my mother had told me stories about people being caned and - my father used to - recite a Scott's poem a Scott's poem about the - teacher taking }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 away a whistle that the wee ha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 d made. And - I was frightened of going, but directly I got there I loved it, and always loved it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well - some of them I was - frightened of and some of th
em I liked. I don't think I had terribly strong feelings, I think on the whole I liked them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did they emphasise anything as important, such as manners, tidiness, punctuality and ways of speaking?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I think probably all those things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
You got a thing called a report. And you had to tell your form mistress and she probably scolded you for getting it. And it also went down on your end of term report. Came back to your parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Your parents would probably be interested in your schoolwork, would they ask what you were doing at school every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes, they did, I promised my mother - she made me promise the day I went that I would always tell her everything that happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did they visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well there was a garden fete in the summer and there was a breaking up at the end of the summer term and they always came to those.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did they ever meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Yes, they did I mean sort of informally but on these occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I think so, yes, mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did the teachers ever single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I - think they - not re
ally, I mean not deliberately but I think they sometimes sort of got their knife in somebody because they thought she washed and - she was always blamed for everything. I think this wasn't - you know, deliberate but it does sort of happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Well not what you'd call gangs, there were - groups that you were friendly with. I mean there'd be three or four people that were special friends and then you might change but - nothing to - it wasn't organised. I
 believe there was a girl in the class below me who was persecuted but - I don't know the details, I - remember the headmistress speaking in a vague way at prayers about how wrong it was that a girl should cry herself to sleep at night. Because she was be
ing persecuted, and I have a sort of an idea that she was in the class below me but I don't really know about it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You don't remember any of the children in your class being left out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No, well there was one who was very unpopular because she was 
very odd, but I rather defended her. And - I think that fluctuated but I think she was - you know I think she was disliked and she knew it, I'm inclined to think now she was a young schizophrenic probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you go on to another school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No, I was always there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You went on to university didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I went to Newnham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I went through a phase of feeling that I'd been pushe
d much too hard into being academic. And I did classics and I went through a phase of feeling that this was absolute death. I mean, as I - in the course of being at Newnham I think I came to feel like that. And I finally changed over and - and took psycho
logy and I think that was the beginning of a - break out into being what I really wanted. But on the other hand I - took up Latin again - when I was fifty-seven to teach it at the Edinburgh \{BLANK\}
 School and liked it very much then, but I think it's differ
ent when you've done something else between but - I think all my sort of - femininity and feeling was being crushed out of me in the - well - for the sake of being academic. I - I mean this is a - a funny thing and it's not a thing that you usually talk a
bout but you know I had a painful period three or four times a year as long as I was doing classics, when I stopped I never had one again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was it psychology that your degree was in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 My first degree was in classics, that was a Cambridge one, and t
hen I - tried teaching and wasn't successful and took a - an MA degree at - Edinburgh, then I took a PhD in psychology at Edinburgh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 While you were at school did you ever have any means of earning money at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 You went to University and then you left and you started teaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I took a year's training as a teacher. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 At a training college?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 At the Cambridge training college. Then I - then I became a teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 How long were you a teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well - I was sacked 
at the end of my first year because I couldn't keep discipline. And I came back to Edinburgh and took the MA degree, and then I tried teaching again, in a very much easier school - the first one was a girls grammar school at Kingston-on-Thames, and the se
cond was a - girls preparatory school at Beaconsfield, I was an awfully nice school, I mean you couldn't possibly sort of blame anything on the school, but I was unsuccessful again and I - I only lasted a term.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 What sort of hours did teachers work at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 I think it was nine 'til probably something like three thirty or four, I don't remember exactly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Can you remember what your pay was at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 It was two hundred and fifty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Was it paid monthly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Monthly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Did you have to put in any extra time, work evenings or Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Well, not - I don't think so at the school but there was a tremendous amount of preparation and correction. And at the Beaconsfield school - I had to look after the boarders, and they ha
d six boarders and - I had to - well supervise their - had to supervise one little boy writing his letter home which he always found very difficult and - and - various other little jobs of that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 When you gave up teaching the second time what did you do next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
Well I took a PHD degree, and then Miss Webb got - oh then I was two years when I didn't quite know what to be because Miss Webb wasn't fit to be left, she was getting old. But I demonstrated in the psychology department and I did a bit 
of tutoring in both psychology and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 classics, this was in Edinburgh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
. And then Miss Webb got so ill that I had to stay at home and nurse her - for fourteen months and then she died. And she left me with enough income, she left all her money to me, I had enou
gh income to live on, if I was very careful, and had about two years when I did small - jobs, tutoring and I did a bit of intelligence testing for the Davidson Clinic, and then - the call up cam}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088  along for the second war and I had to get a job and I became a clerk in an education office in Kent.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 That was just during the war was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 
That was during - that was two years of the war, and then I was - from 1944 to '47 I was a research psychologist at the National Foundation for Educational Research. 
And then I came on to the staff of the Davidson Clinic as Educational psychologist and I was there for nineteen years and - on the whole very happy, I did - all the intelligence testing and remedial teaching that was done and I did a great deal of child p
sycho-therapy. And I went to a union analyst and improved my own problems a bit. And - well in the early days it was very very nice and then actually a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 colleagues was sacked and committ}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 ed suicide and that of course - upset me, but - and I wasn't so happy, but I stayed until I was nearly retiring age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Is the Davidson clinic for mentally disturbed children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 Well it's mostly for adults. It's for both. It's - well the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 
\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 s department died - in about 1967 I think, I left in '66.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 It used to be by the Commonwealth Pool?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 It used to be, yes, and it's now in Hartington Place. Well - the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 
\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 s department faded out because - there's a - clinic at the sick children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3944807\charrsid3623088 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 s hospital as well which is free and I think people went there, actually we never charged - poor people fees at the Davidson clinics so they needn't have worried but - I think people -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6110333 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 It wasn't a residential place then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439624 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16543167\charrsid3623088 No. No, it was - it was for - psychotherapy based on the discoveries of Freud and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
